title: For Sale/Trade:  AWESOME RARE DOUBLE SIDED 4'X3' U.S. MARINES sign! RARE CHANCE!
postcontent:
REVOLUTIONARY WAR, MEXICAN WAR, WAR OF 1812, SPANISH AMERICAN, WAKE,BOXER REBELLION,BATAAN, SAIPAN, NICARAGUA, TARAWA, BATTLE OF BELLEAU WOOD, IWO JIMA, GUADACANAL, OKINAWA, KOREA

TIME TESTED
 U.S. MARINES

MEASURES A COMMANDING 4'H X 3'2"WIDE

I will start this off by saying I really do not want to get rid of this so not entertaining any low ball offers. I am putting this out here to see if there is anyone who HAS to have it just as I did almost 25 years ago.

IF you can find one it will be over a grand but cash wise I would not take that for mine as I will never find another.
If you have some weapons that are worth allot more than what you have in them then that might work out well for both of us.
This sign was framed and presented to a terminally ill Gunny Sgt. and upon his death given to another elderly Marine and I saw it for decades sitting forgotten in a warehouse out of sight and out of mind and it drove me crazy. After decades of asking I was able to finally secure it about 5 years ago.
For some reason today after passing a Marine flag proudly being flown in someones yard I realized that although I have this tremendous tribute in a safe place of honor in my building I am still guilty of it not being in someones possession who would salute the names of the battle it remembers and the brave Marines who made the ultimate sacrifices there.

If I was well off financially I would love to donate this rare tribute but we are not so I will be looking for an offer of cash or cash and trade to pass the torch on to another passionate person.

To save us both some time: Please know that I will not respond to just anyone so please be upfront and to the point on your intentions and offer for a response. 

Absolutely NOT interested in "pickers" or "flippers" out for the fast buck after it took me 20 plus years to secure this highly desirable tribute.

Good intentions for it and a strong offer will get a response.
